---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — okmate.nl" description="Who's behind okmate.nl and why the name is a joke about boring your friends.">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about">
      <span class="tag">About</span>
      <h1>Yeah, the name is a <span class="accent">joke</span>.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        "okmate" is what your friends say &mdash; flatly, eyes already drifting toward
        the door &mdash; when you start explaining how you flew to Lisbon for 12,000 miles
        and a coffee's worth of taxes.
      </p>

      <p>
        okmate.nl is a personal finance and loyalty-points blog for people living in
        the Netherlands. It's about the unglamorous, slightly obsessive craft of making
        your money and your points work a little harder: Albert Heijn Bonus optimization,
        Flying Blue promo awards out of Schiphol, surviving the Belastingdienst as an
        expat, and figuring out which Black Friday "deals" are actually deals.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm not a financial advisor. I'm a person who reads the terms and conditions
        for fun, tracks prices in spreadsheets nobody asked for, and has genuinely
        ruined at least three dinner parties explaining transfer bonuses. This blog
        exists so I can bore the internet instead of the people I love.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul style="color: var(--text-muted); padding-left: 1.4rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        <li><strong>Points &amp; Miles</strong> &mdash; mostly Flying Blue, because Schiphol.</li>
        <li><strong>Financial Hacks</strong> &mdash; small, repeatable, legal money moves.</li>
        <li><strong>Deals</strong> &mdash; with the hype surgically removed.</li>
        <li><strong>Expat Tips</strong> &mdash; the 30% ruling and other Dutch mysteries.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The fine print</h2>
      <p>
        Everything here is opinion and personal experience, not financial advice.
        Rules change &mdash; especially Dutch tax rules, which seem to change for sport.
        Always verify the current details before you make a move. And maybe don't
        bring up koopzegels at the next party. Or do. I'm not your mate. Well. Ok, mate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
